LAB-2-Firewall Rule Logic & policy Enforcement

Step-1
-logged into pfsense web GUI page
-Navigate to Firewall->rules->lancore
-add rules
  *action:pass
  *protocol:any
  *source:ip(192.168.10.1)
  *destination:any
-save any apply changes
Step-2
-next navigate to firewall->rules->lancore
-add rules
  *actiom:block
  *protocol:ICMP
  *source:lancore subnet
  *destination:any
-save and apply changes
Step-3
-next schedule working hours
-navigate to firewall->schedules
-create schedule name toworking_hours
-next select date from mon-fri
-set time range to 9:00 to 17:00
-and click add time configured range
-save the schedule
Step-4
-add schedule to the rule
-navigate to firewall->rules->lancore
-go to advanced options add schedule to working_hours
-saveand apply chnages
Step-5
-navigate to firewall->rule->lancore
-edit the block rule
-tick the log packets that are  handles by this rule
-save and apply chnages
-next verify that logs in status->system logs->firewall
Step-6
-see the blocked traffic
-go to status->sattuslogs->firewall
-identify the blocked entries marked with red
